snippet.textDisplay: Amd has literally brought a new era of pc hardware. In the previous years power like this was unheard of outside of super beefy, thick workstation “laptops”. Now you have it inside of a tiny MacBook sized shell. And when you go down a few tiers you get to a super efficient but still pretty powerful 4 core with Vega graphics that can basically play any game at low settings on very little power, in a tiny form factor. That means we can literally get handheld switch style gaming PCs. I know that dell showed their new 10th gen intel handheld, but a ryzen/Vega version would blow it out of the water. Hell, you could even make bigger more powerful handhelds with the 6 or 8 core variants and more Vega cus that costs an arm and a leg. I think enthusiasts would be interested in a thicker switch like handheld with 8 cores 16 threads, Vega gh, fast soldered ram, nvme, and a 200hz 21:9 screen, and a lithium sulfur battery to keep it powered for long enough to use properly.

And when you go down a few tiers you get to a super efficient but still pretty powerful 4 core with Vega graphics that can basically play any game at low settings on very little power, in a tiny form factor. That means we can literally get handheld switch style gaming PCs. I know that dell showed their new 10th gen intel handheld, but a ryzen/Vega version would blow it out of the water. Hell, you could even make bigger more powerful handhelds with the 6 or 8 core variants and more Vega cus that costs an arm and a leg.
